delhi (1901â€“1925) was an american thoroughbred racehorse that won the 1904 belmont stakes. he was the top money-winner of 1904 and was consequently named the co-historical american champion three-year-old male horse with ort wells. the following year, he was also the historical american champion older male horse, co-champion once again with ort wells. while delhi did have limited success in the stud, he is not considered to be an influential sire.